  <div style="background: #eff6ff; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin: 16px 0;">
    <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600;">💡 The Kanji Tipping Point:</p>
    <p style="margin: 8px 0 0;">Around the 800-1,000 kanji mark, something remarkable happens. New vocabulary becomes <em>easier</em> to learn because you recognize the component characters. The word 図書館 (library) is instantly transparent if you know 図 (diagram), 書 (write), and 館 (building). The hard investment in kanji starts paying dividends.</p>
  </div>

